  "prompt": "Time saving train from mumbai to Darjeeling?",
  "response": "Traveling by train from Mumbai to Darjeeling involves a combination of train journeys and road travel, as there is no direct train to Darjeeling. Here\u2019s a time-saving route you can consider:\n\n1. **Mumbai to New Jalpaiguri (NJP)**: Take a direct train from Mumbai to New Jalpaiguri. Some popular options include:\n   - **Mumbai LTT - Guwahati Express (15645)**: Takes approximately 46 hours.\n   - **Lokmanya Tilak (T) - Kamakhya AC Express (12519)**: Takes around 35-36 hours.\n\n2. **New Jalpaiguri to Darjeeling**:\n   - **Toy Train (Darjeeling Himalayan Railway)**: This is a scenic and historic route but takes around 7-8 hours.\n   - **By Road**: You can take a taxi or shared jeep from NJP to Darjeeling, which takes around 3-4 hours.\n\nConsidering the options, the fastest journey could be taking the Lokmanya Tilak (T) - Kamakhya AC Express to New Jalpaiguri, followed by a road trip to Darjeeling. This would typically take around 40-41 hours in total.\n\nTo ensure the most efficient travel, always check the latest train schedules and road conditions before planning your trip.",
